The logo of Vodafone is seen on the facade of a store in Ronda, Spain, on 3 October 2022. Reuters/Jon NazcaThe National Communications Authority (NCA) approved the sale after Telecel submitted a revised financial and technical proposal in December. The NCA had turned down an initial sale plan submitted by Vodafone Ghana early last year as it did not meet required regulatory standards.The NCA said that the revised proposal provided more clarity on funding required for the transaction and met the regulatory threshold.